Questions:
Which of the following components of the mHealth intervention is considered experimental in this study?
A) Attending regular check-ups with your primary care physician;
B) Receiving weekly messages through a mobile smartphone application with food purchasing recommendations;
C) Shopping at approved grocery stores using a loyalty card;
D) Using a mobile application that tracks your location to send messages when you enter a grocery store.

Correct answer: D

If you decide not to participate in the mHealth Intervention study, which of the following alternatives could you consider for dietary guidance and potential weight loss?
A) Enroll in a different clinical trial focused on exercise for cancer prevention;
B) Seek advice from a registered dietician or pursue behavioral weight loss treatment;
C) Undergo a surgical procedure for weight management;
D) There are no alternatives available outside of the study.

Correct answer: B
